h3cNqa.name: h3cNqa
h3cNqa.contactinfo: Platform Team Huawei 3Com Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.huawei-3com.com Zip:100085
h3cNqa.description: The private mib file includes the test information of the device. It is supplementary for rfc2925.txt.

h3cNqaUdpEcho.name: h3cNqaUdpEcho
h3cNqaUdpEcho.description: Indicates that an implementation is using the UDP based echo server. Notes: The h3cNqaCtlTargetPort and h3cNqaCtlSourcePort need to be set, while in the pingUdpEcho Node, h3cNqaCtlTargetPort must be set to the default value.

h3cNqaTcpconnect.name: h3cNqaTcpconnect
h3cNqaTcpconnect.description: Indicates that an implementation is attempting to connect to a TCP port in order to calculate a round trip time. Notes: The h3cNqaCtlTargetPort and h3cNqaCtlSourcePort need to be set, while in the pingTcpConnectionAttempt Node, h3cNqaCtlTargetPort must be set to the default value.

h3cNqajitter.name: h3cNqajitter
h3cNqajitter.description: Indicates that an implementation is using udp for packet transfers. 'jitter' will cause the NQA(Network Quality Analysis) application to perform delay variance analysis.

h3cNqaHttp.name: h3cNqaHttp
h3cNqaHttp.description: Indicates that an implementation is using udp for name resolution, tcp connect and tcp data transfer mechanisms for HTTP data download from a particular HTTP Server. It causes the NQA application to perform a download of the object specified in the URL.

h3cNqadlsw.name: h3cNqadlsw
h3cNqadlsw.description: Indicates that an implementation is using tcp for sending keepalives. 'dlsw' will cause the NQA application to perform a keepalive operation to measure the response time of a DLSw peer.

h3cNqadhcp.name: h3cNqadhcp
h3cNqadhcp.description: Indicates that an implementation is using udp for sending dhcp requests. 'dhcp' will cause the NQA application to perform an IP Address lease request/teardown operation.

h3cNqaftp.name: h3cNqaftp
h3cNqaftp.description: Indicates that an implementation is using tcp packet for ftp connect and data transfer.

h3cNqaMIBVersion.name: h3cNqaMIBVersion
h3cNqaMIBVersion.description: Version string of this MIB. The format will be: 'Version.Release.Patch: Description' An instance likes: '1.0.0: Initial NQA MIB'

h3cNqaCtlTable.name: h3cNqaCtlTable
h3cNqaCtlTable.description: Defines the NQA Control Extend Table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of performing network analysis operations at a remote host.

h3cNqaCtlEntry.name: h3cNqaCtlEntry
h3cNqaCtlEntry.description: Defines an entry in the h3cNqaCtlTable. The operation of this table is same as that of pingResultsTable.

h3cNqaCtlTargetPort.name: h3cNqaCtlTargetPort
h3cNqaCtlTargetPort.description: The destination port that may be used by udpEcho, tcpConnect and jitter probes.

h3cNqaCtlSourcePort.name: h3cNqaCtlSourcePort
h3cNqaCtlSourcePort.description: The source port that may be used by all tests except for dns and dlsw. If no source port is specified, system will create a random port as source port.

h3cNqaCtlTTL.name: h3cNqaCtlTTL
h3cNqaCtlTTL.description: Specifies the value to store in the TTL Field in the IP packet used to encapsulate the NQA probe.

h3cNqaCtlJitterAdminInterval.name: h3cNqaCtlJitterAdminInterval
h3cNqaCtlJitterAdminInterval.description: Time value in milliseconds that is an interval between two continuous probes in jitter test. This object is only used by jitter test.

h3cNqaCtlJitterAdminNumPackets.name: h3cNqaCtlJitterAdminNumPackets
h3cNqaCtlJitterAdminNumPackets.description: Packet number that specifys how many packets will be sent in one jitter test. This object is only used by jitter test.

h3cNqaCtlHttpOperationType.name: h3cNqaCtlHttpOperationType
h3cNqaCtlHttpOperationType.description: Http operation type: get or post.

h3cNqaCtlHttpOperationString.name: h3cNqaCtlHttpOperationString
h3cNqaCtlHttpOperationString.description: Http operation string. For example, if the http operation type is get, the string will be url, home page and http version.

h3cNqaCtlFtpOperationString.name: h3cNqaCtlFtpOperationString
h3cNqaCtlFtpOperationString.description: Ftp operation string. If the ftp operation type is get, the string must be the file name which will be gotten from ftp server.

h3cNqaCtlVPNInstance.name: h3cNqaCtlVPNInstance
h3cNqaCtlVPNInstance.description: VPN name by which system finds route in the specified VPN to send NQA probe packets.

h3cNqaCtlHistoryKeptTime.name: h3cNqaCtlHistoryKeptTime
h3cNqaCtlHistoryKeptTime.description: To indicate how long the history records will be saved in the pingProbeHistoryTable table after the test stopped.

h3cNqaCtlHistoryEnable.name: h3cNqaCtlHistoryEnable
h3cNqaCtlHistoryEnable.description: To indicate whether the history should be recorded in the PingProbeHistoryTable or not. enabled(1) --history will be recorded disabled(2) --history will not be recorded.

h3cNqaCtlICPIFAdvFactor.name: h3cNqaCtlICPIFAdvFactor
h3cNqaCtlICPIFAdvFactor.description: The advantage factor depends on the type of access and how the service is to be used. This object will be used while calculating the ICPIF (Calculated Planning Impairment Factor) values. Suggestion values: |-----------------------------------|-------| | Service |factor | |-----------------------------------|-------| |conventional wire-line | 0 | |-----------------------------------|-------| |mobility within Building | 5 | |-----------------------------------|-------| |mobility within geographical area | 10 | |-----------------------------------|-------| |access to hard-to-reach location | 20 | |-----------------------------------|-------|

h3cNqaCtlCodecType.name: h3cNqaCtlCodecType
h3cNqaCtlCodecType.description: To indicate the codec type to be used with jitter probe. This is applicable only for the jitter probe.

h3cNqaResultsTable.name: h3cNqaResultsTable
h3cNqaResultsTable.description: Defines the NQA Results Extend Table for providing the capability of performing NQA operations at a remote host. The results of these operations are stored in the h3cNqaResultsTable. The operation of this table is same as that of pingResultsTable.

h3cNqaResultsEntry.name: h3cNqaResultsEntry
h3cNqaResultsEntry.description: The operation of this table is same as that of pingResultsTable.

h3cNqaResultsRttNumDisconnects.name: h3cNqaResultsRttNumDisconnects
h3cNqaResultsRttNumDisconnects.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the destination became disconnected. For connectionless protocol pingCtlTypes, this number should be zero.

h3cNqaResultsRttTimeouts.name: h3cNqaResultsRttTimeouts
h3cNqaResultsRttTimeouts.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the probe timed out.

h3cNqaResultsRttBusies.name: h3cNqaResultsRttBusies
h3cNqaResultsRttBusies.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because all NQA tasks have been running. If a new probe fails to start, the value of this object is incremented. The next test will not start until the next Frequency.

h3cNqaResultsRttNoConnections.name: h3cNqaResultsRttNoConnections
h3cNqaResultsRttNoConnections.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the probe destination is unavailable. For connectionless protocol pingCtlTypes, this number should be zero.

h3cNqaResultsRttDrops.name: h3cNqaResultsRttDrops
h3cNqaResultsRttDrops.description: The number of times that a NQA operation failed to initiated for unavailibility of necessary internal resources.

h3cNqaResultsRttSequenceErrors.name: h3cNqaResultsRttSequenceErrors
h3cNqaResultsRttSequenceErrors.description: The number of packets arrived out of sequence.

h3cNqaResultsRttStatsErrors.name: h3cNqaResultsRttStatsErrors
h3cNqaResultsRttStatsErrors.description: The number of some other errors.

h3cNqaResultsMaxDelaySD.name: h3cNqaResultsMaxDelaySD
h3cNqaResultsMaxDelaySD.description: The maximal delay from source device to destination device. Currently this value is only used for jitter test, and this value must be 0 in other type test. In jitter test, if destination system time is not valid, the SD delay may be set 0.

h3cNqaResultsMaxDelayDS.name: h3cNqaResultsMaxDelayDS
h3cNqaResultsMaxDelayDS.description: The maximal delay from destination device to source device. Currently this value is only used for jitter test, and this value is 0 in other type test. In jitter test, if destination system time is not valid, the DS delay may be set 0.

h3cNqaResultsLostPacketRatio.name: h3cNqaResultsLostPacketRatio
h3cNqaResultsLostPacketRatio.description: The value of this object reflects the drop rate of NQA test. For example, this value is 30 that means source device only had received 70% packets of total sent packets.

h3cNqaResultsPacketLateArrival.name: h3cNqaResultsPacketLateArrival
h3cNqaResultsPacketLateArrival.description: The value of this object indicates the number of the packets that arrived after the timeout.

h3cNqaResultsRttSum.name: h3cNqaResultsRttSum
h3cNqaResultsRttSum.description: The sum of round trip time.

h3cNqaResultsNumOfDelaySD.name: h3cNqaResultsNumOfDelaySD
h3cNqaResultsNumOfDelaySD.description: The number of delay from source to destination that are successfully measured.

h3cNqaResultsMinDelaySD.name: h3cNqaResultsMinDelaySD
h3cNqaResultsMinDelaySD.description: The minimum of all one way times from source to destination.

h3cNqaResultsSumDelaySD.name: h3cNqaResultsSumDelaySD
h3cNqaResultsSumDelaySD.description: The sum of one way times from source to destination.

h3cNqaResultsSum2DelaySD.name: h3cNqaResultsSum2DelaySD
h3cNqaResultsSum2DelaySD.description: The sum of squares of one way times from source to destination.

h3cNqaResultsNumOfDelayDS.name: h3cNqaResultsNumOfDelayDS
h3cNqaResultsNumOfDelayDS.description: The number of delay from destination to source that are successfully measured.

h3cNqaResultsMinDelayDS.name: h3cNqaResultsMinDelayDS
h3cNqaResultsMinDelayDS.description: The minimum of all one way times from destination to source.

h3cNqaResultsSumDelayDS.name: h3cNqaResultsSumDelayDS
h3cNqaResultsSumDelayDS.description: The sum of one way times from destination to source.

h3cNqaResultsSum2DelayDS.name: h3cNqaResultsSum2DelayDS
h3cNqaResultsSum2DelayDS.description: The sum of squares of one way times from destination to source.

h3cNqaJitterStatsTable.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsTable
h3cNqaJitterStatsTable.description: Statistics table for latest jitter activity.

h3cNqaJitterStatsEntry.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsEntry
h3cNqaJitterStatsEntry.description: An entry contains the statistics for the latest jitter activity. This entry is created only if the pingCtlType is h3cNqajitter.

h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfRTT.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfRTT
h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfRTT.description: The number of received destination device responses with which jitter test can reach round-trip time.

h3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesSD.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesSD
h3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the minimal positive jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesSD.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesSD
h3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the maximal positive jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesSD.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesSD
h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesSD.description: The number that records positive jitter times from source to destination in the jitter test. The total number of the value of all positive jitters in packets sent from source to destination.

h3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesSD.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesSD
h3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of positive jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesSD.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesSD
h3cNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of positive jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesSD.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesSD
h3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the minimal absolute values of negative jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesSD.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesSD
h3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the maximal absolute values of negative jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesSD.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesSD
h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesSD.description: The number that records negative jitter times from source to destination in the jitter test. The total number of all negative jitter values in packets sent from source to destination.

h3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesSD.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesSD
h3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of negative jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test. The total number of the value of all negative jitters in packets sent from source to destination.

h3cNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesSD.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesSD
h3cNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of negative jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesDS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesDS
h3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the minimal positive jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesDS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesDS
h3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the maximal positive jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesDS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesDS
h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesDS.description: The number that records positive jitter times from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesDS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesDS
h3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of positive jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesDS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesDS
h3cNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of positive jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesDS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesDS
h3cNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the minimal absolute values of negative jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesDS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesDS
h3cNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the maximal absolute values of negative jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesDS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesDS
h3cNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesDS.description: The number that records negative jitter times from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesDS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesDS
h3cNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of negative jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesDS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesDS
h3cNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of negative jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsPacketLossSD.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsPacketLossSD
h3cNqaJitterStatsPacketLossSD.description: The lost packets number sent from source to destination.

h3cNqaJitterStatsPacketLossDS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsPacketLossDS
h3cNqaJitterStatsPacketLossDS.description: The lost packets number sent from destination to source.

h3cNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesSD.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesSD
h3cNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the average positive jitter value from source to destination.

h3cNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesSD.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesSD
h3cNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the average negative jitter value from source to destination.

h3cNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesDS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesDS
h3cNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the average positive jitter value from destination to source.

h3cNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesDS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesDS
h3cNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the average negative jitter value from destination to source.

h3cNqaJitterStatsPktLossUnknown.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsPktLossUnknown
h3cNqaJitterStatsPktLossUnknown.description: The number of packets which is lost with unknown reason.

h3cNqaJitterStatsOperOfICPIF.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsOperOfICPIF
h3cNqaJitterStatsOperOfICPIF.description: The ICPIF (Calculated Planning Impairment Factor) value for the latest jitter test.

h3cNqaJitterStatsOperOfMOS.name: h3cNqaJitterStatsOperOfMOS
h3cNqaJitterStatsOperOfMOS.description: The MOS (Mean Opinion Score) value for the latest jitter test.

h3cNqaTcpServerTable.name: h3cNqaTcpServerTable
h3cNqaTcpServerTable.description: A table which contains the status of NQA tcp server configuration information.

h3cNqaTcpServerEntry.name: h3cNqaTcpServerEntry
h3cNqaTcpServerEntry.description: A table which contains the status of NQA tcp server configuration information. This entry includes not only the tcp server ip address but also the tcp server port.

h3cNqaTcpServerRowStatus.name: h3cNqaTcpServerRowStatus
h3cNqaTcpServerRowStatus.description: h3cNqaTcpServerIpAddress and h3cNqaTcpServerPort must be set during a creation operation.

h3cNqaUdpServerTable.name: h3cNqaUdpServerTable
h3cNqaUdpServerTable.description: Status of NQA udp server configuration information.

h3cNqaUdpServerEntry.name: h3cNqaUdpServerEntry
h3cNqaUdpServerEntry.description: This entry includes not only the udp server ip address but also the udp server udp port.

h3cNqaUdpServerRowStatus.name: h3cNqaUdpServerRowStatus
h3cNqaUdpServerRowStatus.description: h3cNqaUdpServerIpAddress and h3cNqaUdpServerPort must be set during a creation operation.

h3cNqaStatsMaxGroupNumber.name: h3cNqaStatsMaxGroupNumber
h3cNqaStatsMaxGroupNumber.description: The maximum number saved per group. The maximum value of h3cNqaCtlStatisticsGroupNumber can not exceed the value of this object.

h3cNqaStatisticsCtlTable.name: h3cNqaStatisticsCtlTable
h3cNqaStatisticsCtlTable.description: Defines the NQA statistics control table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of performing NQA operations at a remote host. The results of these operations are stored in the h3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable and the h3cNqaGroupStatsJitterTable.

h3cNqaStatisticsCtlEntry.name: h3cNqaStatisticsCtlEntry
h3cNqaStatisticsCtlEntry.description: Defines an entry in the h3cNqaStatisticsCtlTable. The h3cNqaStatisticsCtlTable has the same index as the pingCtlTable in order for a h3cNqaStatisticsCtlTable to correspond to the pingCtlEntry.

h3cNqaCtlStatisticsInterval.name: h3cNqaCtlStatisticsInterval
h3cNqaCtlStatisticsInterval.description: Statistic information will be calculated after the time that is the value of h3cNqaCtlStatisticsInterval.

h3cNqaCtlStatisticsGroupNumber.name: h3cNqaCtlStatisticsGroupNumber
h3cNqaCtlStatisticsGroupNumber.description: The value of this object indicates the number of group saved. The length of this object is from 1 to h3cNqaStatsMaxGroupNumber.

h3cNqaCtlStatisticsKeptTime.name: h3cNqaCtlStatisticsKeptTime
h3cNqaCtlStatisticsKeptTime.description: To indicate how long the statistic information will be saved after the test stops.

h3cNqaCtlBeginTime.name: h3cNqaCtlBeginTime
h3cNqaCtlBeginTime.description: Time at which the type-specified test will start.

h3cNqaCtlLifeTime.name: h3cNqaCtlLifeTime
h3cNqaCtlLifeTime.description: To indicate how long the type-specified test will last.

h3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable.name: h3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable
h3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable.description: Defines the NQA statistics results table for providing the capability of performing NQA operations at a remote host. The statistics results of these operations in a statistic cycle are stored in the h3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable. The statistic cycle is the value of h3cNqaCtlStatisticsInterval. The first two index identify the pingCtlEntry that the probe statistics result (H3cNqaStatisticsResultsEntry) belongs to.

h3cNqaStatisticsResultsEntry.name: h3cNqaStatisticsResultsEntry
h3cNqaStatisticsResultsEntry.description: Defines an entry in the h3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable. The h3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable has the same index as the pingCtlTable in order for a h3cNqaStatisticsResultsEntry to correspond to the pingCtlEntry that caused it to be created.

h3cNqaStatResIndex.name: h3cNqaStatResIndex
h3cNqaStatResIndex.description: An entry in this table is created when the statistics result of a NQA probe is determined. An implementation MUST start assigning h3cNqaStatResIndex values at 1 and wrap after exceeding the maximum possible value as defined by the limit of this object ('ffffffff'h).

h3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddressType.name: h3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddressType
h3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddressType.description: This object indicates the type of address stored in the corresponding h3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddress object.

h3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddress.name: h3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddress
h3cNqaStatResIpTargetAddress.description: This object represent the host address to be used at a remote host for performing a network analysis operation.

h3cNqaStatResMinRtt.name: h3cNqaStatResMinRtt
h3cNqaStatResMinRtt.description: The minimum NQA probe round-trip-time (RTT) received. The value of 0 for this object implies that no RTT has been received.

h3cNqaStatResMaxRtt.name: h3cNqaStatResMaxRtt
h3cNqaStatResMaxRtt.description: The maximum NQA probe round-trip-time (RTT) received. The value of 0 for this object implies that no RTT has been received.

h3cNqaStatResProbeResponses.name: h3cNqaStatResProbeResponses
h3cNqaStatResProbeResponses.description: The number of responses received. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no probe responses have been received.

h3cNqaStatResSentProbes.name: h3cNqaStatResSentProbes
h3cNqaStatResSentProbes.description: The value of this object reflects the number of probes sent. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no probes have been sent.

h3cNqaStatResRttSumOfSquares.name: h3cNqaStatResRttSumOfSquares
h3cNqaStatResRttSumOfSquares.description: This object contains the sum of the squares for all NQA responses received. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no NQA responses have been received.

h3cNqaStatResStartTime.name: h3cNqaStatResStartTime
h3cNqaStatResStartTime.description: This object contains the start time of the statistic.

h3cNqaStatResInterval.name: h3cNqaStatResInterval
h3cNqaStatResInterval.description: This object contains the interval between two times of statistic.

h3cNqaStatResRttNumDisconnects.name: h3cNqaStatResRttNumDisconnects
h3cNqaStatResRttNumDisconnects.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the destination became disconnected. For connectionless protocol pingCtlTypes, this number should be zero.

h3cNqaStatResRttTimeouts.name: h3cNqaStatResRttTimeouts
h3cNqaStatResRttTimeouts.description: The number of times that a probe failed because the probe timed out.

h3cNqaStatResRttBusies.name: h3cNqaStatResRttBusies
h3cNqaStatResRttBusies.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because errors related to sockets.

h3cNqaStatResRttNoConnections.name: h3cNqaStatResRttNoConnections
h3cNqaStatResRttNoConnections.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the probe destination is unavailable. For connectionless protocol pingCtlTypes, this number should be zero.

h3cNqaStatResRttDrops.name: h3cNqaStatResRttDrops
h3cNqaStatResRttDrops.description: The number of times that a NQA operation failed to initiate for unavailibility of necessary internal resources.

h3cNqaStatResRttSequenceErrors.name: h3cNqaStatResRttSequenceErrors
h3cNqaStatResRttSequenceErrors.description: The number of packets arrived out of sequence.

h3cNqaStatResLostPacketRatio.name: h3cNqaStatResLostPacketRatio
h3cNqaStatResLostPacketRatio.description: The value of this object reflects the drop rate of NQA test packet. For example, if the value is 30, that means source device only had received 70 percent packets of total sent packets.

h3cNqaStatResPacketLateArrival.name: h3cNqaStatResPacketLateArrival
h3cNqaStatResPacketLateArrival.description: The value of this object reflects the number of the packets that arrived after the timeout.

h3cNqaStatResRttSum.name: h3cNqaStatResRttSum
h3cNqaStatResRttSum.description: This object contains the sum of the squares for all NQA responses received during the test lifetime. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no NQA responses have been received.

h3cNqaStatResNumOfDelaySD.name: h3cNqaStatResNumOfDelaySD
h3cNqaStatResNumOfDelaySD.description: The number of one way times from source to destination that are successfully measured.

h3cNqaStatResMinDelaySD.name: h3cNqaStatResMinDelaySD
h3cNqaStatResMinDelaySD.description: The minimum one way times from source to destination.

h3cNqaStatResMaxDelaySD.name: h3cNqaStatResMaxDelaySD
h3cNqaStatResMaxDelaySD.description: The maximum one way times from source to destination.

h3cNqaStatResSumDelaySD.name: h3cNqaStatResSumDelaySD
h3cNqaStatResSumDelaySD.description: The sum of one way times from source to destination.

h3cNqaStatResSum2DelaySD.name: h3cNqaStatResSum2DelaySD
h3cNqaStatResSum2DelaySD.description: The sum of squares of one way times from source to destination.

h3cNqaStatResNumOfDelayDS.name: h3cNqaStatResNumOfDelayDS
h3cNqaStatResNumOfDelayDS.description: The number of one way times from destination to source that are successfully measured.

h3cNqaStatResMinDelayDS.name: h3cNqaStatResMinDelayDS
h3cNqaStatResMinDelayDS.description: The minimum one way times from destination to source.

h3cNqaStatResMaxDelayDS.name: h3cNqaStatResMaxDelayDS

h3cNqaGroupStatsJitterEntry.name: h3cNqaGroupStatsJitterEntry
h3cNqaGroupStatsJitterEntry.description: An entry contains the group statistic information for jitter activity. This entry is created only if the pingCtlType is h3cNqajitter.

h3cNqaStatJitterIndex.name: h3cNqaStatJitterIndex
h3cNqaStatJitterIndex.description: An entry in this table is created when the statistic result of a NQA probe in a statistic cycle is determined. An implementation MUST start assigning h3cNqaStatJitterIndex values at 1 and wrap after exceeding the maximum possible value as defined by the limit of this object ('ffffffff'h).

h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfPosSD.description: The value of time that records the maximal positive jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterNumOfPosSD.name: h3cNqaStatJitterNumOfPosSD
h3cNqaStatJitterNumOfPosSD.description: The number that records positive jitter times from source to destination in the jitter test. The total number of all positive jitter values in packets sent from source to destination.

h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfPosSD.name: h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfPosSD
h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfPosSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of positive jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquarePosSD.name: h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquarePosSD
h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquarePosSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of positive jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfNegSD.name: h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfNegSD
h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfNegSD.description: The value of time that records the minimal absolute values of negative jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfNegSD.name: h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfNegSD
h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfNegSD.description: The value of time that records the maximal absolute values of negative jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterNumOfNegSD.name: h3cNqaStatJitterNumOfNegSD
h3cNqaStatJitterNumOfNegSD.description: The number that records negative jitter times from source to destination in the jitter test. The total number of all negative jitter values sent from source to destination.

h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfNegSD.name: h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfNegSD
h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfNegSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of negative jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquareNegSD.name: h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquareNegSD
h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquareNegSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of negative jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfPosDS.name: h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfPosDS
h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfPosDS.description: The value of time that records the minimal positive jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfPosDS.name: h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfPosDS
h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfPosDS.description: The value of time that records the maximal positive jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterNumOfPosDS.name: h3cNqaStatJitterNumOfPosDS
h3cNqaStatJitterNumOfPosDS.description: The number that records positive jitter times from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfPosDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of positive jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquarePosDS.name: h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquarePosDS
h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquarePosDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of positive jitter values destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfNegDS.name: h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfNegDS
h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfNegDS.description: The value of time that records the minimal absolute values of negative jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfNegDS.name: h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfNegDS
h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfNegDS.description: The value of time that records the maximal absolute values of negative jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterNumOfNegDS.name: h3cNqaStatJitterNumOfNegDS
h3cNqaStatJitterNumOfNegDS.description: The number that records negative jitter times from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfNegDS.name: h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfNegDS
h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfNegDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of negative jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquareNegDS.name: h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquareNegDS
h3cNqaStatJitterSumOfSquareNegDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of negative jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterPacketLossSD.name: h3cNqaStatJitterPacketLossSD
h3cNqaStatJitterPacketLossSD.description: The lost packets number sent from source to destination.

h3cNqaStatJitterPacketLossDS.name: h3cNqaStatJitterPacketLossDS
h3cNqaStatJitterPacketLossDS.description: The lost packets number sent from destination to source.

h3cNqaStatJitterAvePosSD.description: The value of time that records the average positive jitter value from source to destination.

h3cNqaStatJitterAveNegSD.name: h3cNqaStatJitterAveNegSD
h3cNqaStatJitterAveNegSD.description: The value of time that records the average negative jitter value from source to destination.

h3cNqaStatJitterPktLossUnknown.description: The number of packets which is lost with unknown reason.

h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfICPIF.name: h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfICPIF
h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfICPIF.description: The maximum of all ICPIF values in a statistic cycle for jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfICPIF.name: h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfICPIF
h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfICPIF.description: The minimum of all ICPIF values in a statistic cycle for jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfMOS.name: h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfMOS
h3cNqaStatJitterMaxOfMOS.description: The maximum of all MOS values in a statistic cycle for jitter test.

h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfMOS.name: h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfMOS
h3cNqaStatJitterMinOfMOS.description: The minimum of all MOS values in a statistic cycle for jitter test.

h3cNqaReactionTable.name: h3cNqaReactionTable
h3cNqaReactionTable.description: A table of NQA test monitoring notification and reaction configuration definitions. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding pingCtlEntry is deleted.

h3cNqaReactionEntry.name: h3cNqaReactionEntry
h3cNqaReactionEntry.description: Defines an entry in the h3cNqaReactionTable. The first two index elements identify the pingCtlEntry that a h3cNqaReactItemIndex belongs to. The third index element selects a single reaction.

h3cNqaReactOwnerIndex.name: h3cNqaReactOwnerIndex
h3cNqaReactOwnerIndex.description: The first index of h3cNqaReactionTable, it is the same as pingCtlOwnerIndex in pingCtlTable. h3cNqaReactOwnerIndex and h3cNqaReactTestName identify an existed test.

h3cNqaReactTestName.name: h3cNqaReactTestName
h3cNqaReactTestName.description: The second index of h3cNqaReactionTable, it is the same as pingCtlTestName in pingCtlTable. h3cNqaReactOwnerIndex and h3cNqaReactTestName identify an existed test.

h3cNqaReactItemIndex.name: h3cNqaReactItemIndex
h3cNqaReactItemIndex.description: The third index of h3cNqaReactionTable, it definitely identifies one of the reaction configurations for a test.

h3cNqaReactCheckedElement.name: h3cNqaReactCheckedElement
h3cNqaReactCheckedElement.description: A list of reaction condition type. 'probetime' and 'probefailure' are valid when pingCtlType of the test is not h3cNqajitter. 'jitterOwdSD': one way time from source to destination in jitter test. 'jitterOwdDS': one way time from destination to source in jitter test. 'jitterrtt', 'jitterpacketloss', 'jittersd', 'jitterds', 'jitterOwdSD' and 'jitterOwdDS' are valid when pingCtlType of the test is h3cNqajitter. 'icpif' and 'mos' are valid when pingCtlType of the test is h3cNqajitter and h3cNqaCtlCodecType is 'g711Alaw' or 'g711Ulaw' or 'g729A'.

h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit.name: h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit
h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit.description: This object defines an administrative upper-threshold value for h3cNqaReactCheckedElement. The value of this object is zero if h3cNqaReactCheckedElement is specified as 'jitterpacketloss' and 'probefailure'.

h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit.name: h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit
h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit.description: This object defines an administrative lower-threshold value for h3cNqaReactCheckedElement. The value of h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit should be equal or less than the value of h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. The value of this object is zero if h3cNqaReactCheckedElement is specified as 'jitterpacketloss' and 'probefailure'.

h3cNqaReactThresholdType.name: h3cNqaReactThresholdType
h3cNqaReactThresholdType.description: This object defines the reaction threshold types. invalid(0): Invalid value. average(1): If reaction threshold type is average and the average value of watched operation exceeds threshold limit, an action specified in h3cNqaReactActionType is generated when h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. consecutive(2): If reaction threshold type is consecutive and the times of watched operation consecutively exceeds the limit specified by h3cNqaReactThresholdConsecNum, an action specified in h3cNqaReactActionType is generated when h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. accumulative(3): If reaction threshold type is accumulative and the times of watched operation accumulatively exceeds the limit specified by h3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum, an action specified in h3cNqaReactActionType is generated when h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. If reaction threshold type is not configured, the value of this object is 'invalid'.

h3cNqaReactThresholdConsecNum.name: h3cNqaReactThresholdConsecNum
h3cNqaReactThresholdConsecNum.description: This object defines a consecutive threshold limit. The value is zero when h3cNqaReactThresholdType is not 'consecutive'.

h3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum.name: h3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum
h3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum.description: This object defines an accumulative threshold limit. The value is zero when the h3cNqaReactThresholdType is not 'accumulative'.

h3cNqaReactActionType.name: h3cNqaReactActionType
h3cNqaReactActionType.description: Specifies the type of reaction to generate if the specified violation type occurs for the monitored element: none - No reaction is generated trapOnly - A trap is generated triggerOnly - All trigger actions defined for this entry are generated trapAndTrigger - Both a trap and all trigger actions are generated

h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus.name: h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus
h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus.description: Specifies the current status of this reaction entry: invalid - Specifies the reaction entry status is uncertain. overThreshold - Specifies the reaction entry has met the h3cNqaReactThresholdType and the threshold value. belowThreshold - Specifies the reaction entry has disobeyed the h3cNqaReactThresholdType and the threshold value.

h3cNqaReactRowStatus.name: h3cNqaReactRowStatus
h3cNqaReactRowStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
h3cNqaReactRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the h3cNqaReactionTable. Creation of an entry in this table results in a new set of reaction configurations which take effect immediately. Deletion of an entry in this table results in corresponding reaction configurations are being deleted and stop taking effect.

h3cNqaReactCheckedNum.name: h3cNqaReactCheckedNum
h3cNqaReactCheckedNum.description: The number of checked element samples that are monitored.

h3cNqaReactThresholdNum.name: h3cNqaReactThresholdNum
h3cNqaReactThresholdNum.description: The number of checked element samples that are over threshold.

h3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable.name: h3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable
h3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable.description: A table of NQA test monitoring notification and reaction configuration definitions. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding pingCtlEntry is deleted.

h3cNqaStatisticsReactionEntry.name: h3cNqaStatisticsReactionEntry
h3cNqaStatisticsReactionEntry.description: Defines an entry in the h3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable. The first two index elements identify the pingCtlEntry that a h3cNqaReactItemIndex belongs to. The third index element identifies an entry in the h3cNqaStatisticsResultsTable. The forth index element selects a single reaction.

h3cNqaStatReactOwnerIndex.name: h3cNqaStatReactOwnerIndex
h3cNqaStatReactOwnerIndex.description: The first index of h3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable, it is the same as pingCtlOwnerIndex in pingCtlTable.

h3cNqaStatReactTestName.name: h3cNqaStatReactTestName
h3cNqaStatReactTestName.description: The second index of h3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable, it is the same as pingCtlTestName in pingCtlTable.

h3cNqaStatReactIndex.name: h3cNqaStatReactIndex
h3cNqaStatReactIndex.description: The third index of h3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable. An entry in this table is created when the statistics result of a NQA probe is determined. An implementation MUST start assigning h3cNqaStatResIndex values at 1 and wrap after exceeding the maximum possible value as defined by the limit of this object ('ffffffff'h).

h3cNqaStatReactItemIndex.name: h3cNqaStatReactItemIndex
h3cNqaStatReactItemIndex.description: The forth index of h3cNqaStatisticsReactionTable, it definitely identifies one of the reaction configurations for a test

h3cNqaStatReactCheckedNum.name: h3cNqaStatReactCheckedNum
h3cNqaStatReactCheckedNum.description: The number of checked element samples that are monitored.

h3cNqaStatReactThresholdNum.name: h3cNqaStatReactThresholdNum
h3cNqaStatReactThresholdNum.description: The number of checked element samples that are over threshold.

h3cNqaProbeTimeOverThreshold.name: h3cNqaProbeTimeOverThreshold
h3cNqaProbeTimeOverThreshold.description: It is generated when the value of h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. Probe time(equals to RTT for some type of tests) is not in the range h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. 2. The probe time is accumulatively not in the range h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in h3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum. 3. The probe time is consecutively in the range h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in h3cNqaReactThresholdConsecNum. This notification is valid only when h3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is not h3cNqajitter.

h3cNqaJitterRTTOverThreshold.name: h3cNqaJitterRTTOverThreshold
h3cNqaJitterRTTOverThreshold.description: It is generated when the value of h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. The average NQA round-trip-time (RTT) of jitter packets is not in the range h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. 2. The RTT of jitter packets is accumulatively not in the range h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in h3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum in one test. This notification is valid only when h3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is h3cNqajitter.

h3cNqaProbeFailure.name: h3cNqaProbeFailure
h3cNqaProbeFailure.description: It is generated when the value of h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. When the probe test accumulatively failed for a number of times specified in h3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum in one test while the value of h3cNqaReactThresholdType is 'accumulative'. 2. When the probe test consecutively failed for a number of times specified in h3cNqaReactThresholdConsecNum in one test while the value of h3cNqaReactThresholdType is 'consecutive'. This notification is valid only when h3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is not h3cNqajitter.

h3cNqaJitterPacketLoss.name: h3cNqaJitterPacketLoss
h3cNqaJitterPacketLoss.description: It is generated when the value of h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. When the jitter packets accumulatively lost for a number of times specified in h3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum in one test while the value of h3cNqaReactThresholdType is 'accumulative'. This notification is valid only when h3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is h3cNqajitter.

h3cNqaJitterSDOverThreshold.name: h3cNqaJitterSDOverThreshold
h3cNqaJitterSDOverThreshold.description: The SD means the jitter values from source to destination. It is generated when the value of h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. The average of SD in one jitter test is not in the range h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit and the h3cNqaReactThresholdType is specified as 'average' type. 2. The average of SD in one jitter test is accumulatively not in the range h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in h3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum and the h3cNqaReactThresholdType is specified as 'accumulative' type. This notification is valid only when h3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is h3cNqajitter.

h3cNqaJitterDSOverThreshold.name: h3cNqaJitterDSOverThreshold
h3cNqaJitterDSOverThreshold.description: The DS means the jitter values from destination to source. It is generated when the value of h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. The average of DS in one jitter test is not in the range h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit and the h3cNqaReactThresholdType is specified as 'average' type. 2. The average of DS in one jitter test is accumulatively not in the range h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in h3cNqaReactThresholdAccumNum and the h3cNqaReactThresholdType is specified as 'accumulative' type. This notification is valid only when h3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is h3cNqajitter.

h3cNqaICPIFOverThreshold.name: h3cNqaICPIFOverThreshold
h3cNqaICPIFOverThreshold.description: It is generated when the value of h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. When the ICPIF value in one jitter test is not in the range h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. This notification is valid only when h3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger', pingCtlType of the test is h3cNqajitter and h3cNqaCtlCodecType is 'g711Alaw' or 'g711Ulaw' or 'g729A'.

h3cNqaMOSOverThreshold.name: h3cNqaMOSOverThreshold
h3cNqaMOSOverThreshold.description: It is generated when the value of h3cNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. When the MOS value in one jitter test is not in the range h3cNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through h3cNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. This notification is valid only when h3cNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger', pingCtlType of the test is h3cNqajitter and h3cNqaCtlCodecType is 'g711Alaw' or 'g711Ulaw' or 'g729A'.
